'''Mike Kamogelo Sebelebele''' (born 21 July 2002) is a South African soccer player who plays as a winger for [[South African Premiership]] side [[Orlando Pirates]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

== Club career ==

=== TS Galaxy===
Sebelebele played for the TS Galaxy Academy and was promoted to the senior team in March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Raophala |first=Mauwane |date=2025-06-30 |title=TS Galaxy secures Kamogelo Sebelebele's future with lengthy new deal |url=https://farpost.co.za/2025/06/30/ts-galaxy-secures-kamogelo-sebelebeles-future-with-new-deal/ |access-date=2025-12-18 |website=Farpost |language=en-US}}</ref> His breakout season came in the 2024/25 season where he made 29 appearances and scored five goals with two assists.

=== Orlando Pirates ===

He joined [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] before the start of the 2025/26 season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-22 |title=Orlando Pirates new signing Kamogelo Sebelebele tipped to succeed - 'He is an amazing human being' {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/orlando-pirates-new-signing-kamogelo-sebelebele-tipped-to-succeed-he-is-an-amazing-human-being/bltdc357c1c04b68a18 |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He scored scored both goals in the MTN 8 against Sundowns to force the game into penalties where Pirates eventually won.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-16 |title=MTN8: Kamogelo Sebelebele strike rescues Orlando Pirates against Mamelodi Sundowns {{!}} soccer |url=https://www.sabcsport.com/soccer/news/kamogelo-sebelebele-strike-rescues-orlando-pirates-against-mamelodi-sundowns-in-mtn8-thriller |access-date=2025-12-18 |website=SABC |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-25 |title=Orlando Pirates sensation Kamogelo Sebelebele makes a huge promise after stunning Mamelodi Sundowns - 'We know where the MTN8 trophy is going' {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/orlando-pirates-sensation-kamogelo-sebelebele-makes-a-huge-promise-after-stunning-mamelodi-sundowns-we-know-where-the-mtn8-trophy-is-going/blt190e1f550b75a215 |access-date=2025-12-18 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He scored his first league goal for the Buccaneers when he scored the winning goal in a 1–0 win against [[Stellenbosch F.C.|Stellenbosch]] where he later received the August goal of the month award for this strike.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-20 |title=Finally off the mark! Kamogelo Sebelebele delivers as Orlando Pirates bag first Premier Soccer League points with win over Stellenbosch FC {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/finally-off-the-mark-kamogelo-sebelebele-delivers-as-orlando-pirates-bag-first-premier-soccer-league-points-with-win-over-stellenbosch-fc/blt690b6d7688cf63c6 |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rabothe |first=Tshepo |date=2025-09-04 |title=Tinkler, Sebelebele & Dithejane bag monthly awards for August |url=https://farpost.co.za/2025/09/04/tinkler-sebelebele-dithejane-bag-monthly-awards-for-august/ |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=Farpost |language=en-US}}</ref> 

== International career ==
He competed for the [[South Africa national soccer B team|South Africa A team]] at the [[2025 COSAFA Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hendricks |first=Joshua |date=2025-07-14 |title=Orlando Pirates snatch COSAFA star in stunning transfer coup |url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/sport/soccer/psl-south-africa/orlando-pirates-snatch-cosafa-star-in-stunning-transfer-coup/ |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=The South African |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He got his [[South Africa national soccer team|senior]] call up for the World Cup qualifiers against [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] and [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] in September 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-02 |title=Sebelebele & Shabalala's First Words In Bafana Camp |url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/psl/bafana/kamogelo-sebelebele-mduduzi-shabalala-open-up-on-being-bafana-bafana-squad |access-date=2025-12-09 |website=Soccer Laduma |language=en}}</ref>

